<TITLE> CHT to get 23% rise in allocation </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)The proposed budget for the fiscal year 2008-09 has seen a 23 percent increase in allocations for the Chittagong Hill Tracts region. Allocations for the Ministry of Chittagong Hill Tract affairs has been proposed at Tk 577 crore, of which Tk 330 crore is for development expenditure, while the remaining Tk 247 crore is for non-development expenditure. The current fiscal year's budget for the CHT has an allocation of Tk 469 crore, with Tk 256 crore and Tk 213 crore in development and non-development expenditures respectively. In his budget speech Monday, finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam said socio-economic activities in the region such as education initiatives, sanitation programmes, improved water supply and mother and childcare projects are ongoing. "Under rural development projects, ongoing programmes relating to micro-credit operations, vocational training, employment generation and socio-economic development will continue next year," said the adviser. However, allocations to finance three development assistance programs in the hill tracts has been reduced to Tk 80 crore, from Tk 105 crore in the current fiscal year's revised budget. bdn
